<subSubSection id="5DB49D69095E00051C70B115CEC10188" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CA68BEE9CF87956A650487CDDDFDA88C" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="35888A9A22E2E60D7D91BB495F1FD97B" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Surstylus bifid, the upper lobe with about 5 thin, peg-like prensisetae and 1 fine seta, the below one with 1 thin, peg-like prensiseta and 2 fine setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CF4E521A59C63372F36FA838AFD8832B" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7A, B</figureCitation>
); gonopods undeveloped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EE01EF0302D6CA5F9C757DBF4AF7968F" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D30C27C364A28DA16C81FF3BCE0AC9FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph id="9C948E95A4F1CE300B28A907F476F80D" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E250B96B22FE08CD7C23F2301FF6D27C" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
(♂, ♀) 
<emphasis id="BDCEF9DCD36D4387421DF14B3DDBA757" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A2C00E841F1E679689560C40A42022E4" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3A</figureCitation>
): Frons yellowish brown. Pedicel and first flagellomere maple. Facial carina yellowish, short, 1/3 length as face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E0FABBC96CE57DE061BC9389FF48740" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="4A3BD91D5987A9F9B69860AC86CDA05E" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="42E4B121F5E081DB2DC1D0605203F6E7" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3C, E</figureCitation>
): Mesonotum and scutellum yellowish. Acrostichal setulae in ca 8 regular rows. Wings hyaline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="68BA56503354D92380E9D12678235CC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="7314A844F60C11FCD02145C37FBBE283" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E392A60248891C9AC7F8EDD8A536319F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3C, E</figureCitation>
): Tergites and sternites yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B6B826212863128991F0B2FA268D62F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="EA22C873BC5008455CFA47D001A6ADC9" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male terminalia</emphasis>
: Epandrium with ca 14 setae near posterior margin and ventral corner on each side (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="50E5E367EFABF68B3EF073164308D07B" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7A, B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium glabrous (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="45BA2DF4F937E8CB871F9211313F03DC" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7C, D</figureCitation>
). Paramere slender and curved apically, with 3 sensillae subbasally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="578D36C0DEFF2D97F36864E87630951A" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00A61C1CF65E8AF0638906FBE2B041F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="AB65B513F88855A6537AEE71570EF90F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Female terminalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B331738BDA0A4B6946A7BC627622FB07" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7E</figureCitation>
): Oviscapt with 2 long subapical trichoid ovisensilla, 17 peg-like ovisensilla on each side on ventral margins and 5 trichoid ovisensilla on dorsal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A9DF4BF3E0D90536B5E1574DA27F400" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="CBDB1C161D76884727BFB91CE8292A59" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Measurements</emphasis>
(range in 2♂, 1♀, in mm): BL = (1.73-2.07, 1.93 mm), ThL = (0.80-1.07, 0.80), WL = (1.80-2.27, 1.93), WW = (0.67-0.93, 0.80).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="52FB7ACCD988618480EB7A4C74F9178C" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="E95D7D9A1D8998DA054B74957B307D2F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Indices</emphasis>
: arb = 2/1, avd = 0.60-1.00, adf = 2.00-2.50, flw = 2.00, FW/HW = 0.45-0.48, ch/o = 0.08, prorb = 0.80-0.83, rcorb = 0.40-0.60, vb = 0.33-0.50, dcl = 0.54-0.60, presctl = 0.45-0.60, sctl = 1.00-1.10, sterno = 0.67-0.75, orbito = 0.67-0.75, dcp = 0.30-0.40, sctlp = 0.83, C = 2.42-2.92, 4c = 1.00-1.20, 4v = 2.17-2.60, 5x = 1.50-2.00, ac = 2.40-3.00, M = 0.67-0.80, C3F = 0.25-0.33.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
